events.name: BigData with BigQuery - the Data Warehousing for analytics at any scale
events.description:
• What we'll do
Please come join us for a walk-through about BigQuery and how this service can help companies of all sizes. There will be multiple Googlers to help answer questions and work with you. This will be held in the Google office downtown. Looking forward to connecting!

Snacks and beverages will be provided. "BigQuery is Google's serverless, highly scalable, low cost enterprise data warehouse designed to make all your data analysts productive. Because there is no infrastructure to manage, you can focus on analyzing data to find meaningful insights using familiar SQL and you don't need a database administrator. BigQuery enables you to analyze all your data by creating a logical data warehouse over managed, columnar storage as well as data from object storage, and spreadsheets."

events.name: Extracting Java Microservices with Kubernetes
events.description:
Join Google Cloud Premier Partner, Dev9 and their VP of Delivery / GCP Certified Architect , Mike Ensor, for a discussion and live demonstration on using Kubernetes to extract java microservices from monoliths. Learn about different technical approaches and the importance of bounded context in java microservices. Followed by a live demonstration of two primary extraction methods: Strangler Pattern and Service Extraction.

Key Takeaways:
-Importance of understanding bounded context in microservices
-Two demonstrable methods for microservice extraction
-Practical example of Kubernetes usage

RSVP: Attendance is limited to first 35 confirmed guests.

Speaker:
Mike Ensor - VP of Delivery / Google Certified Architect at Dev9, www.dev9.com
Mike is a hands-on software architect with 24 years of experience in cloud architectures, custom application development, e-commerce,, distributed systems and big data implementations. Throughout his career he has continually pushed the use of test-driven development, the principles of continuous delivery and emphasized the merits of Agile-based development. Mike has co-presented with Google / K8 luminaries such as Kelsey Hightower, Alan Naim and Carter Morgan.

events.name: Model Behavior: Google Cloud Functions, Machine Learning, & the Model Server
events.description:
Details:

At Caravel, engineers are building conversational AI for eCommerce stores — work that heavily relies on serverless functions and machine learning models.

Due to the limitations of serverless functions, it often
doesn't make sense to load the machine learning models directly in the cloud function.

In this talk, Hannes is sharing Caravel's work in integrating machine learning in Google Cloud functions. He is outlining how models are
hosted on a model server and how the serverless endpoints can interact with the model server.

This solution allows Caravel to scale to ever-changing demands for their applications, but still provide the full machine learning functionality.

About the speaker:

Hannes Hapke is the VP of Engineering and AI at Caravel (caravelapp.com). Caravel's applications are built on serverless functions and a good number of machine learning models. Hannes is a Google Developer Expert and a co-author of machine learning publications like NLP in Action and upcoming O'Reilly publication on Machine Learning Workflows.

Schedule:

Doors Open at 5:45 p.m.
Programming to begin at 6:15 p.m. with Q&A after.

Drinks and Light Snacks will be served.

**Interested in speaking at a future event? Message us and let us know! We'd love to have you.**

events.name: PDX Google Cloud Run Club
events.description:
Please register using the official sign up link below!!!
https://events.withgoogle.com/cloud-run-club-portland/
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Welcome to Cloud Run Club, PDX Edition!

Cloud Run Club is an event for developers to learn about Google’s new serverless container-based compute platform Cloud Run.

Come network with Googlers and other community members and learn more about Cloud Run. The event will include tech talks, hands-on labs, an optional fun-run on the RUN LOCATION, and food & drinks. We will also have some running swag like t-shirts, socks and sweatbands for the attendees.

Speakers:
- Mark Chmarny, Google Cloud - Technical Program Manager for Serverless.
- Special Guest TBD

What is Cloud Run?

Cloud Run is a managed compute platform that enables you to run stateless containers that are invocable via HTTP requests. Cloud Run is serverless: it abstracts away all infrastructure management, so you can focus on what matters most — building great applications. It is built from Knative, letting you choose to run your containers either fully managed with Cloud Run, or in your Google Kubernetes Engine cluster with Cloud Run on GKE.

Read more about Cloud Run - https://cloud.google.com/run/

Venue
Google Portland office, Wells Fargo Building
Address: 309 SW 6th Ave, Floor 4 - Portland, OR 97204

Registration is required to attend this event.
Spots are limited, please sign up ahead of time.

events.name: EdgeLink Tech Event - Kelsey Hightower Speaking Engagement
events.description:
For those interested, Kelsey Hightower from Google Cloud will be speaking in downtown Portland tonight! Information below. Event is being run by EdgeLink.

https://www.meetup.com/EdgeLink-Events/events/264060245/

On Tuesday, October 15th 2019 EdgeLink will be hosting a special event for Portland’s Cloud Technology professionals. Kelsey Hightower of Google will be the keynote speaker covering Cloud Native technologies and how individuals and companies alike can leverage them. Topics will include how to evaluate, adapt and migrate to the ever changing world of technology. This event will be an opportunity to learn from one of the brightest minds in cloud technology and how your organization can utilize emerging tech more productively and efficiently. We hope you can join us for this educational event. The first 30 individuals to sign up will receive a “swag bag” in addition to food and beverage provided by EdgeLink to all attendees.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Kelsey Hightower is a Principal Developer Advocate at Google working on Google’s Cloud Platform. He has helped develop and refine many Google Cloud Products including Google’s Kubernetes Engine, Cloud Functions, and Apigees’s API Gateway. Kelsey spends most of his time with executives and developers spanning the global fortune 1000 helping them understand and leverage Google technologies and platforms to grow their businesses.

Kelsey is also a huge open source contributor and currently maintains multiple projects that aid software developers and operations professionals in building and shipping cloud native applications. He is also an accomplished author and keynote speaker with a knack for demystifying complex topics and enabling others to succeed.

Kelsey is also known for his work in the community and was the inaugural winner of the CNCF Top Ambassador award for his work in helping bootstrap the Kubernetes community. He is also a mentor and technical advisor helping founders turn their visions into reality.
